---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Projects" tagline="● The research, put to work"
  description="What I am building — AI infrastructure, agents, education, and a public prediction ledger.">
  <div class="wrap">
    <section class="page-intro">
      <div class="kicker">Applied work</div>
      <h1>The research isn't only <em>on the page.</em></h1>
      <p class="deck">It shows up as ventures and builds — an AI agent platform, sovereign-infrastructure strategy, and education that closes the design-layer gradient. Each one is a framework with skin in the game.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="blk" style="border-bottom:none">
      <div class="proj">
        <div class="pcell">
          <div class="t"><span>Venture · AI agent platform</span><span class="yr">2024 →</span></div>
          <h2>Afrigent</h2>
          <div class="role">Founder · loop engineering in production</div>
          <p>An agent platform built to put the trust primitives to work — <b>verification, audit trails, and escalation</b> as first-class features, not afterthoughts. The thesis from the Agentic Systems line, shipped.</p>
          <div class="chips"><span class="tag">orchestration</span><span class="tag">trust primitives</span><span class="tag">Africa</span></div>
          <div class="links"><a class="lk" href="#">Visit →</a><a class="lk" href="#">Case note →</a></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pcell"><div class="placeholder"><span>screenshot — Afrigent dashboard</span></div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="proj">
        <div class="pcell"><div class="placeholder"><span>diagram — sovereign compute stack</span></div></div>
        <div class="pcell">
          <div class="t"><span>Strategy · sovereign infrastructure</span><span class="yr">2025 →</span></div>
          <h2>Akinke</h2>
          <div class="role">Advisor · rent-vs-own compute</div>
          <p>Sovereign-infrastructure strategy for compute ownership — turning the <b>Rent-vs-Own</b> and <b>Sovereign Compute Stack</b> frameworks into actual siting, power, and capital decisions for regions choosing to own.</p>
          <div class="chips"><span class="tag">energy</span><span class="tag">capex</span><span class="tag">policy</span><span class="tag">Alberta</span></div>
          <div class="links"><a class="lk" href="#">Overview →</a></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="proj">
        <div class="pcell">
          <div class="t"><span>Education · design-layer</span><span class="yr">2025 →</span></div>
          <h2>Closing the gradient</h2>
          <div class="role">Curriculum · who AI serves</div>
          <p>Education aimed squarely at the design layer — the place where knowledge gradients are set. Built to put more people on the steep side of the slope, where systems get shaped rather than just used.</p>
          <div class="chips"><span class="tag">design layer</span><span class="tag">access</span><span class="tag">curriculum</span></div>
          <div class="links"><a class="lk" href="#">Syllabus →</a></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pcell">
          <div class="t"><span>Open · the method itself</span><span class="yr">2025 →</span></div>
          <h2>The Ledger</h2>
          <div class="role">Open source · built in public</div>
          <p>The prediction ledger has its own repo. Predictions, falsifiers, and scores — <b>versioned in public</b>, so the method can be forked, critiqued, and run by anyone.</p>
          <div class="chips"><span class="tag">open source</span><span class="tag">epistemics</span></div>
          <div class="links"><a class="lk" href="/ledger">Open ledger →</a><a class="lk" href="https://github.com/chiKeka/ledger">Repo →</a></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .proj{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:0;border:1.5px solid var(--ink);border-bottom:none}
  .proj:last-of-type{border-bottom:1.5px solid var(--ink)}
  .pcell{padding:38px 36px;border-right:1px solid var(--rule);position:relative}
  .pcell:last-child{border-right:none}
  .pcell .t{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.12em;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:14px;display:flex;justify-content:space-between}
  .pcell .t .yr{color:var(--dim)}
  .pcell h2{font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(30px,3.6vw,46px);line-height:1.02;letter-spacing:-.01em;margin-bottom:6px}
  .pcell .role{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12px;color:var(--dim);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.06em;margin-bottom:18px}
  .pcell p{font-size:17px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--ink2);margin-bottom:14px;max-width:52ch}
  .pcell p b{color:var(--ink);font-weight:500}
  .pcell .chips{display:flex;gap:8px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:18px}
  .pcell .placeholder{height:100%;min-height:260px;background:repeating-linear-gradient(135deg,var(--paper2) 0 14px,var(--paper3) 14px 28px);border:1px dashed var(--rule2);display:flex;align-items:flex-end;justify-content:flex-start;padding:18px}
  .pcell .placeholder span{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;color:var(--dim);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.1em;background:var(--paper);padding:5px 9px;border:1px solid var(--rule)}
  .pcell .links{margin-top:18px;display:flex;gap:14px;flex-wrap:wrap}
  .pcell .lk{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em;border-bottom:1.5px solid var(--accent);padding-bottom:2px}
  @media(max-width:820px){.proj{grid-template-columns:1fr}.pcell{border-right:none;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule)}.pcell .placeholder{min-height:180px}}
</style>
